  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Resilience by Strengthening Disaster Preparedness in Dominica</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project contributes to improving the capacity of disaster management authorities to manage displacement and mobility in the context of disasters at a national level in Dominica. Relevant activities include rehabilitation of collective centres and pre-positioning of non-food items. In addition, the project works to support disaster management authorities to integrate the needs of marginalised populations and currently excluded groups including persons with disabilities, migrants and displaced individuals into disaster risk management (DRM) plans. In particular, IOM is conducting research of best practices and lessons learned on specific conditions of vulnerability in past disasters and inclusivity of the DRM systems in Dominica.  IOM will disseminate research findings and provide multi-stakeholder and thematic consultations on inclusiveness in DRM.  IOM will adapt and develop training, awareness raising and simulation exercise materials to include specific groups.</narrative>
  </description>
